        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 29 at 4:58PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 457 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
East Bend, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Pilot Mountain...
East Bend...
King...
Pilot Mountain State Park...
Siloam...
Pinnacle...
and Hanging Rock State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
